# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# Firebase setup secrets — service-account JSON, downloaded client SDK
# configs (google-services.json / GoogleService-Info.plist). Regenerable
# via scripts/firebase/firebase_setup.sh (§11.4.77). NEVER git-versioned
# (§11.4.10 / §11.4.10.A).
scripts/firebase/secrets/

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# Superpowers SDD controller scratch (ledger, not source)
.superpowers/

# pandoc/weasyprint PDF-engine temp artifacts
toPdfViaTempFile*
.claude/
.claude/
submodules/open-design/

# Helm chart dependencies — build derivatives, regenerable via `helm dependency build`
# (Chart.yaml + Chart.lock are the tracked source of truth). §11.4.30 / §11.4.77
infrastructure/helm/**/charts/*.tgz

# Flutter build-tool generated artifacts (regenerated by `flutter pub get` / build). §11.4.30
clients/flutter/.dart_tool/
clients/flutter/build/
clients/flutter/.flutter-plugins
clients/flutter/.flutter-plugins-dependencies
clients/flutter/android/
clients/flutter/ios/
clients/flutter/linux/
clients/flutter/macos/
clients/flutter/windows/
clients/flutter/web/
clients/flutter/**/.dart_tool/
clients/flutter/**/build/
# Flutter golden-mismatch dumps + container pub-cache mount targets (never versioned). §11.4.30
clients/flutter/test/failures/
clients/flutter/**/test/failures/
clients/flutter/.pubcache/
clients/flutter/.pub-cache/

# Agent worktree scratchpad — evidence + temp files, never versioned. §11.4.11 / §11.4.30
scratchpad/

# §11.4.93/§11.4.95 workable-items SQLite SSoT: docs/workable_items.db itself
# is TRACKED (authoritative source data, NOT a build artifact — §11.4.95,
# NEVER add it here). Only its transient WAL/SHM sidecars are ignored; a
# WAL-checkpoint (`PRAGMA wal_checkpoint(TRUNCATE)`) runs before every
# commit-stage per §11.4.95 so these are always safely discardable.
docs/workable_items.db-wal
docs/workable_items.db-shm

# Ephemeral runtime/QA evidence (raw §11.4.128 corpus + §11.4.202 reporting evidence); curated proof lives under docs/qa/
/qa-results/

# Agent git worktrees — never versioned in the parent (survive on disk)
.worktrees/
